# -*- mode: org -*-
#+TITLE: dosname: C++11 literal-suffix build breaks + memory bugs
#+DATE: 2026-06-20

* DONE [#A] dosname: g++-14 build breaks and latent memory bugs  :dosname:build:memory:cxx:
  RESOLUTION (2026-06-20). Module builds clean under the strict flags; smoke
  test renames "My Long File.txt" -> "mylonfil.txt" (8.3, collision-safe) with no
  crash.
  - MfFile.cc:144,175: literal-suffix fixed (="%" FMT_CARD32=).
  - Renamer.cc:358: literal-suffix fixed and the collision suffix now uses a
    bounded snprintf into the named dosNameSize buffer.
  - Renamer.cc:316: the "."/".." path now allocates via newstr() instead of
    strcpy into the NIL curDosName; isupper/tolower take (unsigned char).
  - MfFile.cc:526 textContents: NULL-check malloc (close file, return 0 on OOM).
  - MfFile.cc:239 compareFirstBlock: return 2 (incomparable) when either fBlock
    is NULL instead of memcmp on NULL.
  - MfFile.cc:194 size(): on stat failure return 0 instead of caching/returning
    MAX_CARD32 as a usable length.
  - CapWord.cc:160 analyzeRun: terminate at run[j] (chars actually copied), not
    run[size]; NULL-check the malloc.
  - MfLink.cc:110: readlink bounded to BUFSIZ-1 and linkbuf NUL-terminated.
  - ADDITIONAL build-blocker found once the above unblocked the module:
    dosname.cc:218-219 silent/force set-but-unused. These flags (-s/--silent,
    -f/--force) are documented but were never wired into the MfDirectory
    copy/link methods (which take no such parameters). Kept accepting them for
    backward compatibility as explicit (void) no-ops; actually implementing the
    semantics is deferred feature work (noted in-source).
  Deferred (low): the remaining CARD32<->INT32 -Wconversion sites did not fire
  under the current flag set (no -Wsign-conversion); left as-is.
  Full-tree review 2026-06-20 (g++ 14, C++11+, strict flags). dosname renames
  files to DOS 8.3 names and links the common C++ libs (bplib/bclib). bplib uses
  *unsigned* lengths/indices, so =if(x<0)= guards are dead and =len-other=
  underflows. See [[build-system]] and [[common-integration]] (bplib/bclib API
  use verified consistent with the installed headers).

** Build-blockers (-Werror=literal-suffix, C++11)

*** [critical] MfFile.cc:144, :175 — invalid suffix on literal
=fscanf(output,"%"FMT_CARD32,...)= : =FMT_CARD32= expands to ="u"= with no space,
so C++11 lexes ="%"u= as a user-defined-literal token.
Fix: add a space: ="%" FMT_CARD32=.

*** [critical] Renamer.cc:358 — same literal-suffix defect (NOT in the original error list)
=sprintf(p,"%03"FMT_INT32,n)= -> ="%03"d=. Same fix: ="%03" FMT_INT32=.

** Memory safety (latent)

*** [high] MfFile.cc:526 — textContents(): unchecked malloc
=data=malloc((fsize+1))= is used by =fread=/=data[fsize]= with no NULL check.
Fix: check =data==NULL= and bail like the other paths.

*** [high] MfFile.cc:239 — compareFirstBlock(): memcmp on possibly-NULL fBlock
=loadFirstBlock()= leaves =fBlock=NULL= on failure, but =compareFirstBlock=
does =memcmp(fBlock,otherFile->fBlock,...)= unconditionally.
Fix: guard =if(fBlock && otherFile->fBlock)=.

*** [high] CapWord.cc:160 — analyzeRun(): uninitialized gap + wrong terminator
=size=cNext-mark= counts all chars, but the copy loop skips ignore-class chars
leaving =j<size=; it then writes =run[size]='\0'= instead of =run[j]='\0'=, so
=run[j..size-1]= are garbage. Any name with ignore chars (=* + / ? = > \=)
produces a corrupt run.
Fix: terminate at =run[j]='\0'=.

*** [medium] Renamer.cc:316 — computeDosName(): write to never-allocated curDosName
In the =processedUN[0]=='.'= branch, =strcpy(curDosName,processedUN)= runs but
=curDosName= is only =malloc='d in the =else=; here it is still NIL.
Fix: allocate before the strcpy.

*** [medium] Renamer.cc:351 — collision suffix can overflow the 13-byte buffer
=curDosName=malloc(8+1+3+1)=13=; appending ='.'= then =sprintf(p,"%03...",n)=
when the name already uses 8.3 writes past the 13 bytes.
Fix: size for the worst case, or bound the name part before suffixing.

*** [medium] MfFile.cc:194 — size() returns MAX_CARD32 on stat failure, used as a length
=loadFirstBlock= then computes =wordCount=(MAX_CARD32+3)/4 ~ 1G= -> =malloc(~4GB)=;
=textContents= does =malloc(MAX_CARD32+1)= -> wraps to =malloc(0)=.
Fix: treat =MAX_CARD32= as an error in callers.

*** [low] MfLink.cc:110 — readlink result not NUL-terminated
Safe today (=read()= uses an explicit count) but any later =strlen(linkbuf)=
over-reads. NUL-terminate after =readlink=.

** Signed/unsigned (-Wconversion)
Pervasive =CARD32=<->=INT32= mixing will trip =-Wconversion=/=-Wsign-conversion=
if those are enabled: Renamer.cc:543 =INT32 c=keys->size()=, MfDirectory.cc:480,534
=INT32 c=contentCard()= (both sources return CARD32), and =malloc(size+1)=
(INT32->size_t) in CapWord.cc. Harmless for realistic counts.

** Health
Will not compile until the three literal-suffix errors (MfFile.cc:144,175 and the
unlisted Renamer.cc:358) are fixed. Beyond the build, the unchecked
=textContents= malloc, NULL-=fBlock= memcmp, the never-allocated =curDosName=
dot-path, the 13-byte collision overflow, and =analyzeRun= mis-termination are
genuine and worth fixing before trusting the tool on real data.
